					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It's better because you have to load 1 value, and then do a PLA loop to do the optimized loop (Whatever that is called again), but if you keep all 3 arrays at the beginning of $0100, so you don't have to reposition any pointer at all while you would putting them other places. Now an array of LDA STA in WRAM would be better, but most games don't use it so I figured it'd be useless to mention. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

